00:22:12.710 --> 00:22:15.040
Hello and welcome to HITRECORD.

00:22:15.040 --> 00:22:17.720
I'm Joe. I started this
place a long time ago

00:22:17.720 --> 00:22:19.140
with my brother, Dan.

00:22:19.140 --> 00:22:21.710
And it's a little bit different
than your typical internet,

00:22:21.710 --> 00:22:23.380
social network kind of thing.

00:22:23.380 --> 00:22:26.120
The point here isn't to keep
in touch with your friends

00:22:26.120 --> 00:22:28.920
or to follow celebrities or even

00:22:28.920 --> 00:22:31.850
to showcase something
you made on your own.

00:22:31.850 --> 00:22:35.650
The point here is to
make things together.

00:22:35.650 --> 00:22:40.290
HITRECORD is a new kind
of production company,

00:22:40.290 --> 00:22:42.780
and we produce all
kinds of art and media.

00:22:42.780 --> 00:22:44.780
We've played short
films at film festivals.

00:22:44.780 --> 00:22:45.600
We published books.

00:22:45.600 --> 00:22:46.620
We put out records.

00:22:46.620 --> 00:22:50.830
We made a TV show that won
an Emmy, and our website

00:22:50.830 --> 00:22:52.970
and our mobile app is
designed to allow anybody

00:22:52.970 --> 00:22:57.100
to come join this community and
contribute to those productions.

00:22:57.100 --> 00:22:59.670
And yes, any time one of
our productions makes money,

00:22:59.670 --> 00:23:02.810
the contributors
get fairly paid.

00:23:02.810 --> 00:23:05.590
So, certainly, if you are
an artist of any kind,

00:23:05.590 --> 00:23:09.160
if you're a writer, a filmmaker,
musician, graphic artist,

00:23:09.160 --> 00:23:11.030
photographer, illustrator,
animator, editor,

00:23:11.030 --> 00:23:12.820
or anything, come work with us.

00:23:12.820 --> 00:23:15.670
Or even if you don't
fancy yourself an artist

00:23:15.670 --> 00:23:18.900
but you've got a good story to
tell or just something to say,

00:23:18.900 --> 00:23:20.390
that can make a great
inspiration

00:23:20.390 --> 00:23:21.430
for one of our projects.

00:23:21.430 --> 00:23:23.810
If you've got good taste and
you want to give feedback

00:23:23.810 --> 00:23:26.520
on the stuff we're making here,
if you want to curate the things

00:23:26.520 --> 00:23:29.600
that you see on here that you
like, that's really valuable.

00:23:29.600 --> 00:23:32.070
Or if you don't want to do
any of that, and you just want

00:23:32.070 --> 00:23:34.180
to hang out and watch
how it happens

00:23:34.180 --> 00:23:36.740
and maybe meet a few cool
people, that's all right too.

00:23:36.740 --> 00:23:39.400
But it's really fun
if you join in.

00:23:39.400 --> 00:23:40.530
Now, how does this all work?

00:23:40.530 --> 00:23:41.560
Where do you get started?

00:23:41.560 --> 00:23:42.470
One good place to start is

00:23:42.470 --> 00:23:44.130
with what we call
creative challenges.

00:23:44.130 --> 00:23:47.050
So this is for those times
when you know you want

00:23:47.050 --> 00:23:48.670
to do something creative,

00:23:48.670 --> 00:23:50.810
but you don't know exactly
what you want to do.

00:23:50.810 --> 00:23:52.580
This site will serve
you up a whole bunch

00:23:52.580 --> 00:23:54.590
of different challenges,
and you'll find probably

00:23:54.590 --> 00:23:57.770
at least one that inspires
you at that moment in time.

00:23:57.770 --> 00:24:00.090
I issue a lot of the
challenges as do the fine folks

00:24:00.090 --> 00:24:01.350
who work here in this office,

00:24:01.350 --> 00:24:03.630
but anybody can issue
their own challenges.

00:24:03.630 --> 00:24:06.360
So, for example, say you
shot a bunch of footage,

00:24:06.360 --> 00:24:08.170
and you're looking
for a video editor,

00:24:08.170 --> 00:24:10.480
you can upload your raw footage
and then issue a challenge

00:24:10.480 --> 00:24:12.390
to editors and say,
"Here's all my footage.

00:24:12.390 --> 00:24:13.560
Let's see you guys
cut it together."

00:24:13.560 --> 00:24:16.740
Which brings us to remix.

00:24:16.740 --> 00:24:17.950
So when you upload
something here,

00:24:17.950 --> 00:24:20.830
everybody else has permission
to download it, sample it,

00:24:20.830 --> 00:24:23.160
revise it, refine it,
build on top of it,

00:24:23.160 --> 00:24:24.550
and upload their new version.

00:24:24.550 --> 00:24:27.470
So, for example, say you're
a singer and you're looking

00:24:27.470 --> 00:24:30.170
for an instrumental to sing
on top of, there's tons

00:24:30.170 --> 00:24:32.500
of great instrumental pieces
of music on HITRECORD,

00:24:32.500 --> 00:24:36.210
and you can write a
song on top of that.

00:24:36.210 --> 00:24:42.360
If you're an animator, you
can go find an illustration,

00:24:42.360 --> 00:24:44.150
download it, put in
the after effects,

00:24:44.150 --> 00:24:45.720
and turn it into
some kind of cartoon.

00:24:45.720 --> 00:24:49.270
Writers, you know that good
writing is in the rewriting.

00:24:49.270 --> 00:24:51.520
So if you see something on
the site that you like --

00:24:51.520 --> 00:24:53.000
this is a good piece of writing,

00:24:53.000 --> 00:24:55.340
but I have a different
idea for it, do that.

00:24:55.340 --> 00:24:56.210
Write a new draft.

00:24:56.210 --> 00:24:56.700
Punch it up.

00:24:56.700 --> 00:24:57.650
Add some jokes.

00:24:57.650 --> 00:24:58.410
Change the ending.

00:24:58.410 --> 00:25:01.400
Think of this as a huge
worldwide writer's room.

00:25:01.400 --> 00:25:05.570
So now comes the question:
how does all of that lead

00:25:05.570 --> 00:25:07.380
to a cohesive, finished product?

00:25:07.380 --> 00:25:10.100
So I, as well as other folks
who work here in this office,

00:25:10.100 --> 00:25:13.200
we're always on the lookout for
stuff coming through our site

00:25:13.200 --> 00:25:16.180
that we can sort of take to
the traditional marketplace.

00:25:16.180 --> 00:25:18.870
Who decides which projects
become productions,

00:25:18.870 --> 00:25:22.160
and who has sort of final cut on
how those productions turn out?

00:25:22.160 --> 00:25:23.970
It's a simple answer,
and it's me.

00:25:23.970 --> 00:25:26.300
I'm the director of
this production company.

00:25:26.300 --> 00:25:29.290
But, like every great director
that I've ever worked with,

00:25:29.290 --> 00:25:32.290
I know that, as a director,
I'm nothing without the artists

00:25:32.290 --> 00:25:33.200
that I'm collaborating with.

00:25:33.200 --> 00:25:34.080
Now, like I said before,

00:25:34.080 --> 00:25:35.530
when one of our productions
makes money,

00:25:35.530 --> 00:25:38.670
we do pay the contributing
artists, and I'm proud to say,

00:25:38.670 --> 00:25:41.390
since 2010, we've paid different
contributing artists all

00:25:41.390 --> 00:25:46.670
over the world almost
$2 million dollars.

00:25:46.670 --> 00:25:51.420
So, I know nobody wants to
join another internet thing.

00:25:51.420 --> 00:25:54.320
