00:27:41.240 --> 00:27:43.780
as a media production company.

00:27:43.780 --> 00:27:46.550
Obviously, I'm pretty
interested in the topic

00:27:46.550 --> 00:27:49.030
of intellectual property.

00:27:49.030 --> 00:27:52.710
I'm glad we're dedicating
a day to talking about it.

00:27:52.710 --> 00:27:54.910
I actually think the
way that we figure

00:27:54.910 --> 00:27:58.180
out how intellectual property
is going to work today

00:27:58.180 --> 00:28:00.040
and especially how it's
going to work moving

00:28:00.040 --> 00:28:04.170
in the future is going to be
a huge part of us succeeding

00:28:04.170 --> 00:28:07.310
as a -- as a human race.

00:28:07.310 --> 00:28:12.950
So one thing I'll say is in the
past, I used to be of one mind,

00:28:12.950 --> 00:28:16.310
which is, the whole notion that
information wants to be free

00:28:16.310 --> 00:28:18.340
and that anything you can
put into ones and zeroes

00:28:18.340 --> 00:28:21.080
because you can just copy it
as many times as you want,

00:28:21.080 --> 00:28:22.310
it shouldn't cost anything.

00:28:22.310 --> 00:28:23.900
It shouldn't be worth money.

00:28:23.900 --> 00:28:28.080
And my mind really changed
a lot a couple of years ago.

00:28:28.080 --> 00:28:30.730
And it was largely this one
book that got me thinking

00:28:30.730 --> 00:28:32.390
of it differently that
I really recommend.

00:28:32.390 --> 00:28:34.580
And the book is called
Who Owns the Future?

00:28:34.580 --> 00:28:36.790
And it's by a writer
named Jaron Lanier.

00:28:36.790 --> 00:28:37.790
His contention is

00:28:37.790 --> 00:28:40.200
that intellectual
property is worth money,

00:28:40.200 --> 00:28:44.520
and it has to be worth money
for capitalism to keep working.

00:28:44.520 --> 00:28:47.840
Right now, this sort of
notion or you might say,

00:28:47.840 --> 00:28:51.100
the myth that intellectual
property is not worth money,

00:28:51.100 --> 00:28:54.810
has largely decimated the music
industry, is doing quite a bit

00:28:54.810 --> 00:28:58.820
of damage to the field of
journalism, but moving forward,

00:28:58.820 --> 00:29:02.480
it could damage so much more
than just those industries.

00:29:02.480 --> 00:29:04.890
And another thing
that Mr. Lanier points

00:29:04.890 --> 00:29:07.100
out is digital information,

00:29:07.100 --> 00:29:09.320
intellectual property,
it is worth money.

00:29:09.320 --> 00:29:10.710
It does generate money.

00:29:10.710 --> 00:29:13.830
It's just that right now, when
we're sort of under the illusion

00:29:13.830 --> 00:29:15.760
that it's free, all
of the money,

00:29:15.760 --> 00:29:18.510
all of the value generated by
that intellectual property,

00:29:18.510 --> 00:29:23.230
is just going to a few big
internet giants like Google,

00:29:23.230 --> 00:29:26.700
Facebook, etc. because
those companies sort

00:29:26.700 --> 00:29:31.830
of trade information, getting
information to its consumers

00:29:31.830 --> 00:29:35.190
for free while advertising to
them and making tons and tons

00:29:35.190 --> 00:29:37.970
and tons of money because
they're not compensating the

00:29:37.970 --> 00:29:39.630
people who generated
the information

00:29:39.630 --> 00:29:40.430
that they're delivering.

00:29:40.430 --> 00:29:43.810
And so the notion that
intellectual property

00:29:43.810 --> 00:29:45.760
in the digital form
is not worth money,

00:29:45.760 --> 00:29:47.400
that's something I
think we need to sort

00:29:47.400 --> 00:29:49.200
of get past and get over.

00:29:49.200 --> 00:29:52.560
It has to be worth money in
order for our economy to work.

00:29:52.560 --> 00:29:56.520
I'll give you another example,

00:29:56.520 --> 00:29:58.550
and that's my company,
HITRECORD.

00:29:58.550 --> 00:29:59.790
We make all kinds of things.

00:29:59.790 --> 00:30:03.830
We make short films and
music, books, made a TV show,

00:30:03.830 --> 00:30:06.840
and our company is sort of
founded on the principle

00:30:06.840 --> 00:30:09.630
that yeah, actually the
artists who do contribute

00:30:09.630 --> 00:30:10.980
to these things, even
though they're making their

00:30:10.980 --> 00:30:13.630
contributions digitally,
they deserve to be paid,

00:30:13.630 --> 00:30:15.950
and that if we make
money as a company,

00:30:15.950 --> 00:30:18.260
HITRECORD compensates
the artists

00:30:18.260 --> 00:30:21.950
and the contributors whose
intellectual property generates

00:30:21.950 --> 00:30:23.070
that value.

00:30:23.070 --> 00:30:25.180
I'm not saying everybody
should do it this way,

00:30:25.180 --> 00:30:27.750
but this is a way that
we have found to work.

00:30:27.750 --> 00:30:30.370
Over the last five or six years
that we've been doing this,

00:30:30.370 --> 00:30:32.440
we've paid out almost $2 million

00:30:32.440 --> 00:30:34.660
to different artists
all over the world.

00:30:34.660 --> 00:30:36.230
It's been a beautiful
thing for me.

00:30:36.230 --> 00:30:38.850
A lot of people who get paid

00:30:38.850 --> 00:30:40.840
from HITRECORD productions
have never been paid

00:30:40.840 --> 00:30:43.020
for their art before, and
that's a wonderful feeling.

00:30:43.020 --> 00:30:47.860
Even besides the actual amount
of money, just the principle

00:30:47.860 --> 00:30:51.960
of getting paid, it
feels validating,

00:30:51.960 --> 00:30:55.260
and I think the folks who
do get paid, they deserve

00:30:55.260 --> 00:30:58.310
to feel validated because
their contribution helps

00:30:58.310 --> 00:30:59.430
to make money.

00:30:59.430 --> 00:31:02.830
We designed our terms
of service to do this.

00:31:02.830 --> 00:31:05.390
We have a unique legal
agreement that everybody

00:31:05.390 --> 00:31:08.610
who joins our site and
contributes to our projects

00:31:08.610 --> 00:31:10.300
because they've clicked
a box and they've agreed

00:31:10.300 --> 00:31:12.670
to these terms of service,
and this terms of service lays

00:31:12.670 --> 00:31:14.620
out this methodology of payment.

00:31:14.620 --> 00:31:16.910
That's also important,
having fair

00:31:16.910 --> 00:31:19.560
and transparence in
terms of service.

00:31:19.560 --> 00:31:23.240
It not only helps the members
of our community who are able

00:31:23.240 --> 00:31:26.110
to get paid for their work,
it helps us as a company.

00:31:26.110 --> 00:31:30.150
I definitely think the trust
that we earned by having fair

00:31:30.150 --> 00:31:33.120
and transparent terms of service
has really benefitted us.

00:31:33.120 --> 00:31:36.580
But again, it goes back
to the principle then.

00:31:36.580 --> 00:31:38.900
Just because somebody's
contribution is digital,

00:31:38.900 --> 00:31:40.410
doesn't mean it's
not worth money.

00:31:40.410 --> 00:31:45.140
And if some work that
someone did made money,

00:31:45.140 --> 00:31:47.440
then they deserve to get paid.

00:31:47.440 --> 00:31:48.680
I'll leave it there.

00:31:48.680 --> 00:31:49.790
Thanks for listening.

00:31:49.790 --> 00:31:51.630
And again, thanks
for having this day,

00:31:51.630 --> 00:31:53.860
talking about intellectual
property.

00:31:53.860 --> 00:31:59.570
I think it's something really
well worth talking about.

00:31:59.570 --> 00:32:01.510
Thanks again.

