00:32:24.170 --> 00:32:28.130
And I'm super happy
to be here and honored

00:32:28.130 --> 00:32:32.070
to have been chosen
to be a part of this.

00:32:32.070 --> 00:32:34.330
My name is Anna Metcalfe.

00:32:34.330 --> 00:32:38.000
And I'm originally from
Virginia, but in 2006,

00:32:38.000 --> 00:32:41.540
I moved to Minneapolis where
I graduated with my MFA

00:32:41.540 --> 00:32:45.400
in Ceramics from the
University of Minnesota.

00:32:45.400 --> 00:32:52.360
My personal work ranges from
public art, installation,

00:32:53.650 --> 00:32:59.380
community engagement,
and dinnerware.

00:32:59.380 --> 00:33:00.820
I'm also an educator.

00:33:00.820 --> 00:33:03.850
I teach ceramics at the
University of Minnesota,

00:33:03.850 --> 00:33:07.990
and I also teach business skills
to artists all over the Midwest

00:33:07.990 --> 00:33:11.070
with an organization called
Springboard for the Arts.

00:33:12.090 --> 00:33:14.980
I'm here this morning
as one of three founders

00:33:14.980 --> 00:33:17.550
of a web-based startup
called Gather Art Registry.

00:33:17.550 --> 00:33:21.910
We are in our ninth
month of our first year.

00:33:21.910 --> 00:33:25.630
We were friends long before
we were business partners,

00:33:25.630 --> 00:33:28.650
and we had a lightbulb
moment one day.

00:33:28.650 --> 00:33:32.730
My now business partner, Rachel,
was purchasing a ceramic piece

00:33:32.730 --> 00:33:34.720
for me for a friend's wedding.

00:33:34.720 --> 00:33:36.270
And as I was wrapping
up the gift

00:33:36.270 --> 00:33:39.210
on my front porch,
she made a comment.

00:33:39.210 --> 00:33:41.520
"Couples should be able to
register for art they know

00:33:41.520 --> 00:33:44.280
and love for their weddings,
and I should be able to buy it

00:33:44.280 --> 00:33:46.840
for them just like I can
buy towels and toasters

00:33:46.840 --> 00:33:49.660
from Macy's online registry."

00:33:49.660 --> 00:33:52.320
I said "Yes, they should.

00:33:52.320 --> 00:33:54.240
That should be a thing.

00:33:54.240 --> 00:33:56.380
And it should be carefully
curated and presented

00:33:56.380 --> 00:34:00.530
to highlight the value of the
art in our community to buyers."

00:34:00.530 --> 00:34:02.100
So that got us wondering.

00:34:02.100 --> 00:34:05.960
What if it was possible for
people to register for local art

00:34:05.960 --> 00:34:08.030
for their wedding, and what

00:34:08.030 --> 00:34:10.900
if an online registry platform
could make it really easy

00:34:10.900 --> 00:34:13.700
for their friends and family
to buy couples handmade gifts?

00:34:13.700 --> 00:34:16.190
And that is how Gather was born.

00:34:16.190 --> 00:34:21.210
It combines three
basic ingredients: art,

00:34:21.210 --> 00:34:22.840
wedding gifts, and the internet.

00:34:22.840 --> 00:34:28.150
We learned how to write a
business plan after that.

00:34:28.150 --> 00:34:32.160
We began contracting with local
artists, and in early 2014,

00:34:32.160 --> 00:34:34.480
we started Gather LLC.

00:34:34.480 --> 00:34:38.990
After an Indiegogo
campaign in late 2014,

00:34:38.990 --> 00:34:43.240
we launched our registry
in the summer of 2015.

00:34:43.240 --> 00:34:46.870
Now, midway through our
first wedding season,

00:34:46.870 --> 00:34:49.090
we're in the process of
adding to our collection

00:34:49.090 --> 00:34:51.890
and expanding our audience.

00:34:51.890 --> 00:34:56.330
This is an example of a
product page on our site.

00:34:56.330 --> 00:35:01.590
To create -- our mission is
pretty simple actually --

00:35:01.590 --> 00:35:05.300
it's to create a new market
for artists and their work.

00:35:05.300 --> 00:35:07.490
It's to provide a platform
that meets the demands

00:35:07.490 --> 00:35:11.040
of a new generation of
shoppers and art collectors.

00:35:11.040 --> 00:35:14.580
And it's also to educate new
audiences about the value

00:35:14.580 --> 00:35:18.900
of art and handmade crafts.

00:35:18.900 --> 00:35:22.860
I personally curate our
collection from artists

00:35:22.860 --> 00:35:25.460
from around Minnesota
and Wisconsin.

00:35:25.460 --> 00:35:28.040
We offer items like what
you see in this image:

00:35:28.040 --> 00:35:32.450
hand forged bottle openers
from antique wrenches,

00:35:32.450 --> 00:35:34.500
laser etched coasters,

00:35:34.500 --> 00:35:38.290
hand carved mugs,
and original prints.

00:35:38.290 --> 00:35:40.150
We also make it possible
for couples

00:35:40.150 --> 00:35:44.160
to commission original work
from their favorite artists.

00:35:44.160 --> 00:35:46.170
Erin and Jay, who got
married last August,

00:35:46.170 --> 00:35:49.620
wanted to commission Minneapolis
artist, Nicholas Harper,

00:35:49.620 --> 00:35:51.990
to paint an original
work for them based

00:35:51.990 --> 00:35:56.310
on their favorite novel called
Geek Love by Katherine Dunn.

00:35:56.310 --> 00:35:59.280
He obliged, and after
reading the book,

00:35:59.280 --> 00:36:02.630
he created a painting based
on two of the main characters

00:36:02.630 --> 00:36:05.010
who happen to be Siamese twins.

00:36:05.010 --> 00:36:08.680
It was a very interesting
collaboration.

00:36:08.680 --> 00:36:10.650
This is an image
of the unveiling

00:36:10.650 --> 00:36:13.820
that we had last month.

00:36:13.820 --> 00:36:16.720
Like any small business, our
path is filled with discoveries

00:36:16.720 --> 00:36:19.270
and challenges that lead
us to make adjustments

00:36:19.270 --> 00:36:23.380
that benefit both
artists and our customers.

00:36:23.380 --> 00:36:27.760
However, like artists, we find
ourselves navigating systems

00:36:27.760 --> 00:36:29.460
and structures that
have been constructed

00:36:29.460 --> 00:36:32.570
by software engineers
and marketplaces

00:36:32.570 --> 00:36:37.940
that don't always take the arts
or artists into consideration.

00:36:37.940 --> 00:36:41.090
Our mission is to create
an easy to navigate bridge

00:36:41.090 --> 00:36:43.710
between the wedding industry
and the creative work of artists

00:36:43.710 --> 00:36:45.710
through an ecommerce platform.

00:36:45.710 --> 00:36:50.730
Our challenges are a result of
the potential incompatibilities

00:36:50.730 --> 00:36:53.970
between creative
tendencies and audiences

00:36:53.970 --> 00:36:55.160
that understand the value

00:36:55.160 --> 00:36:57.920
as being produced
by big box stores.

00:36:57.920 --> 00:37:02.300
What is true for artists -- that
creativity requires an abundance

00:37:02.300 --> 00:37:06.190
of time, the willingness to be
open to unexpected outcomes,

00:37:06.190 --> 00:37:08.870
and that innovation
requires constant change --

00:37:08.870 --> 00:37:10.350
are actually the very things

00:37:10.350 --> 00:37:12.600
that make our mission
challenging in a marketplace

00:37:12.600 --> 00:37:18.270
that demands fast turnarounds,
consistency, and predictability.

00:37:18.270 --> 00:37:22.510
Where an artist finds
time to be an asset,

00:37:22.510 --> 00:37:29.380
our customers are looking for
shortcuts and fast shipping.

00:37:29.380 --> 00:37:30.740
Where an artist --

00:37:30.740 --> 00:37:34.010
where constant change is a
positive marker for growth

00:37:34.010 --> 00:37:34.920
in an artist's career,

00:37:34.920 --> 00:37:39.790
our customers are
depending on consistency.

00:37:42.870 --> 00:37:49.190
Where artists seek
the unexpected,

00:37:49.190 --> 00:37:52.010
our customers don't tend

00:37:52.010 --> 00:37:54.180
to appreciate surprises
in the same way.

00:37:54.180 --> 00:38:01.310
So our task is to work enough
within systems and the markets

00:38:01.310 --> 00:38:04.790
that encourage entrepreneurship
in the arts all while continuing

00:38:04.790 --> 00:38:07.950
to support individual artists
to do what they do best.

00:38:07.950 --> 00:38:11.520
We are fully aware that our job
is not to convert the masses

00:38:11.520 --> 00:38:14.600
into art supporters,
but we are also aware

00:38:14.600 --> 00:38:18.110
that even art consumers
live in the same world

00:38:18.110 --> 00:38:22.090
that covets convenience,
and we would be foolish

00:38:22.090 --> 00:38:24.520
to ignore the opportunities

00:38:24.520 --> 00:38:27.730
that the Internet has
provided to small businesses.

00:38:27.730 --> 00:38:30.420
Whether that means we have to
tweak the online platform we use

00:38:30.420 --> 00:38:32.640
to make it work for original art

00:38:32.640 --> 00:38:36.320
or repackage a traditional
concept for our clients,

00:38:36.320 --> 00:38:38.670
Gather is a matchmaker
between the arts

00:38:38.670 --> 00:38:40.280
and the rest of the world.

00:38:40.280 --> 00:38:43.220
Our hope is that
with time and effort,

00:38:43.220 --> 00:38:44.980
the systems will be more willing

00:38:44.980 --> 00:38:48.010
to accommodate a different
version of productivity

00:38:48.010 --> 00:38:51.340
and value as offered
by individual artists.

00:38:51.340 --> 00:38:52.930
Thank you all again
for having me,

00:38:52.930 --> 00:38:56.510
and happy Intellectual
Property Day.

