three things, and then I'm going

00:40:53.890 --> 00:40:55.020
to tell you what I told you.

00:40:55.020 --> 00:40:58.670
So the first thing is that
my goal here is to share

00:40:58.670 --> 00:41:01.570
with you all what is
happening on the streets.

00:41:01.570 --> 00:41:06.290
We represent a vast sort of
different spectrum of creators.

00:41:06.290 --> 00:41:09.830
And it's my hope to come to
Washington and share a message

00:41:09.830 --> 00:41:13.300
that the world, the
laws, have to sort

00:41:13.300 --> 00:41:15.730
of be consistently evolving.

00:41:15.730 --> 00:41:18.530
So the point one here is
that we are all hyphens.

00:41:18.530 --> 00:41:22.010
I started out -- first of
all, I dropped out of --

00:41:22.010 --> 00:41:24.360
well, I bailed on a career
in professional soccer,

00:41:24.360 --> 00:41:25.550
bailed on medical school,

00:41:25.550 --> 00:41:28.070
and dropped out of a
Ph.D. in Philosophy.

00:41:28.070 --> 00:41:28.910
My poor parents.

00:41:28.910 --> 00:41:32.170
Right? In order to
become a photographer.

00:41:32.170 --> 00:41:36.810
That's very strange for
the people in my family.

00:41:36.810 --> 00:41:40.760
But I was a photographer,
and then I figured out how

00:41:40.760 --> 00:41:43.180
to be a photographer, and then
I figured out how to make money.

00:41:43.180 --> 00:41:44.790
So I became sort of
a business person.

00:41:44.790 --> 00:41:46.340
And then I became a director.

00:41:46.340 --> 00:41:48.380
I started directing
videos and short films

00:41:48.380 --> 00:41:49.780
and television commercials.

00:41:49.780 --> 00:41:51.860
And then I was a guest speaker.

00:41:51.860 --> 00:41:53.690
I keynoted all over the world,

00:41:53.690 --> 00:41:55.800
and then I was the
author of three books.

00:41:55.800 --> 00:42:00.490
In 2009, I created
the first iPhone app

00:42:00.490 --> 00:42:03.190
that shared photos
to social networks.

00:42:03.190 --> 00:42:05.690
So it was pre-Instagram.

00:42:05.690 --> 00:42:07.500
We had millions of users.

00:42:07.500 --> 00:42:09.170
And it fundamentally helped

00:42:09.170 --> 00:42:13.360
to shape the photo-sharing
economy that you know today.

00:42:13.360 --> 00:42:14.790
Now, that was by a photographer.

00:42:14.790 --> 00:42:17.380
My photo studio became
a little incubator.

00:42:17.380 --> 00:42:19.790
Again, millions of
downloads all over the world,

00:42:19.790 --> 00:42:23.210
and that was the App
of the Year in 2009.

00:42:23.210 --> 00:42:25.200
That is a fundamental
sort of shift.

00:42:25.200 --> 00:42:28.510
So I was a software
developer then.

00:42:28.510 --> 00:42:30.740
And that helped me
understand how technology

00:42:30.740 --> 00:42:32.580
and creativity can
work together.

00:42:32.580 --> 00:42:35.580
So in 2010, we spawned
this little company called

00:42:35.580 --> 00:42:38.330
CreativeLive out of a room that
was a third the size of this

00:42:38.330 --> 00:42:41.940
with the goal of educating
the world's creators.

00:42:41.940 --> 00:42:45.230
So I took an audience of a
million people that I had built

00:42:45.230 --> 00:42:49.390
over the course of five years
and put them in connection

00:42:49.390 --> 00:42:52.640
with my peers, who are the
best photographic, design,

00:42:52.640 --> 00:42:53.930
music educators in the world,

00:42:53.930 --> 00:42:55.410
and that company is
called CreativeLive.

00:42:55.410 --> 00:42:58.960
Our first class had
50,000 people in it.

00:42:58.960 --> 00:43:00.180
And today, we're the largest,

00:43:00.180 --> 00:43:02.010
live streaming education
company in the world.

00:43:02.010 --> 00:43:04.790
We reach millions of
creators all over the world.

00:43:04.790 --> 00:43:06.710
We've raised about $40 million.

00:43:06.710 --> 00:43:08.710
We've had more than
two billion minutes

00:43:08.710 --> 00:43:11.390
of creative education
consumed on a video platform.

00:43:11.390 --> 00:43:12.620
So what am I now?

00:43:12.620 --> 00:43:13.950
Am I a CEO?

00:43:13.950 --> 00:43:16.120
Am I a founder?

00:43:16.120 --> 00:43:18.690
Am I a company guy?

00:43:18.690 --> 00:43:19.970
What am I?

00:43:19.970 --> 00:43:21.260
The point is we're all hyphens.

00:43:21.260 --> 00:43:22.860
There's like 15 different
things,

00:43:22.860 --> 00:43:26.610
and we used to be just one
thing, and now, we are many.

00:43:26.610 --> 00:43:28.330
So that's point one.

