00:50:34.630 --> 00:50:35.910
And so my first question is -

00:50:35.910 --> 00:50:38.970
I just want to give the audience
some background information

00:50:38.970 --> 00:50:39.920
about you.

00:50:39.920 --> 00:50:42.030
And could you tell
everybody what is it

00:50:42.030 --> 00:50:44.110
that brought you to the arts?

00:50:44.110 --> 00:50:48.130
And I'd like to start with Anna.

00:50:48.130 --> 00:50:52.720
&gt;&gt; Gosh, I actually didn't
consider myself an artist

00:50:52.720 --> 00:50:54.070
for a really long time.

00:50:54.070 --> 00:50:57.550
There is something intimidating
about calling myself an artist.

00:50:57.550 --> 00:51:00.780
And I think it was probably
when I went to graduate school

00:51:00.780 --> 00:51:03.520
to get my Masters of
Fine Art that I decided

00:51:03.520 --> 00:51:04.960
to call myself an artist.

00:51:04.960 --> 00:51:06.160
But I think ultimately,

00:51:06.160 --> 00:51:09.440
it wasn't even a
choice that I made.

00:51:09.440 --> 00:51:14.380
It was simply making
the inevitable choice

00:51:14.380 --> 00:51:18.430
and material -- I'm a
ceramic artist, and so,

00:51:18.430 --> 00:51:23.340
getting my hands actually in
material, transforming material,

00:51:23.340 --> 00:51:29.060
fire, and food -- those kinds of
things have always compelled me,

00:51:29.060 --> 00:51:32.060
and I think, will
probably continue

00:51:32.060 --> 00:51:35.540
to compel not only
the work that I make

00:51:35.540 --> 00:51:37.770
but then also how I
connect with communities,

00:51:37.770 --> 00:51:42.320
which I think is truly
what now compels me

00:51:42.320 --> 00:51:46.000
about being an artist,
which is communicating

00:51:46.000 --> 00:51:49.840
and effectively giving voice
to a lot of different people.

00:51:49.840 --> 00:51:51.530
&gt;&gt; Great, thanks.

00:51:51.530 --> 00:51:52.050
Chase?

00:51:52.050 --> 00:51:54.340
&gt;&gt; I'd love -- I'll
reference two words,

00:51:54.340 --> 00:51:55.810
sort of community and voice.

00:51:55.810 --> 00:51:56.970
That was really important to me.

00:51:56.970 --> 00:51:59.600
I felt a dramatic pressure,

00:51:59.600 --> 00:52:02.480
and I don't think it
was family specific.

00:52:02.480 --> 00:52:06.490
Maybe a little bit, but when
I was growing up, it was -

00:52:06.490 --> 00:52:09.970
"the creative kid"
was a weird moniker.

00:52:09.970 --> 00:52:11.100
And so I ran the other way.

00:52:11.100 --> 00:52:12.590
I became the captain
of the football team

00:52:12.590 --> 00:52:14.030
because I wanted
to sort of fit in.

00:52:14.030 --> 00:52:16.630
I ended up going to college
on a soccer scholarship,

00:52:16.630 --> 00:52:23.000
but my whole sort of being was
in conflict, and ultimately,

00:52:23.000 --> 00:52:27.410
the ability to create
something is a thing

00:52:27.410 --> 00:52:28.650
that is uniquely human.

00:52:28.650 --> 00:52:31.800
It differentiates us from almost
every species on the planet,

00:52:31.800 --> 00:52:34.220
the ability to have a voice
for underserved community,

00:52:34.220 --> 00:52:36.580
for connection, for empathy.

00:52:36.580 --> 00:52:40.970
To me, that was something that
if I could figure out a way

00:52:40.970 --> 00:52:44.960
to get paid would make
this a life worth living.

00:52:44.960 --> 00:52:47.090
I think again I referenced
earlier people saying

00:52:47.090 --> 00:52:49.130
in this room that they don't
think of themselves as creative.

00:52:49.130 --> 00:52:52.510
Everything in this room -- it's
a pretty beige room honestly -

00:52:52.510 --> 00:52:56.750
but was created by no
one who was no smarter

00:52:56.750 --> 00:52:59.620
or no creative than anyone else.

00:52:59.620 --> 00:53:02.190
It's really about
unlocking that creativity.

00:53:02.190 --> 00:53:06.720
And if I could play a role in
that for myself and ultimately,

00:53:06.720 --> 00:53:08.570
I've learned later in my
career, that's what I want to do

00:53:08.570 --> 00:53:12.150
for others, that it would
be a life well lived.

00:53:12.150 --> 00:53:15.660
So it's sort of a calling but
more than anything, an awareness

00:53:15.660 --> 00:53:18.950
that this is one of
the reasons we're here.

